{
  "bookId": "laozi-wangbi-wiki",
  "num": 27,
  "title": "第二十七章",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "善行無轍迹，"
    },
    {
      "text": "善言無瑕讁；"
    },
    {
      "text": "善數不用籌策；"
    },
    {
      "text": "善閉無關楗而不可開，善結無繩約而不可解。"
    },
    {
      "text": "是以聖人常善救人，故無棄人；"
    },
    {
      "text": "常善救物，故無棄物，是謂襲明。故善人者，不善人之師；"
    },
    {
      "text": "不善人者，善人之資。"
    },
    {
      "text": "不貴其師，不愛其資，雖智大迷，"
    },
    {
      "text": "是謂要妙。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "順自然而行，不造不始，故物得至而無轍迹也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "順物之性，不別不析，故無瑕讁可得其門也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 7
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "因物之數，不假形也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 20
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "因物自然，不設不施，故不用關楗繩約而不可開解也。此五者皆言不造不施，因物之性，不以形制物也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 4,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 14
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "聖人不立形名以檢於物，不造進向以殊棄不肖，輔萬物之自然而不為始，故曰無棄人也。不尚賢能，則民不爭，不貴難得之貨，則民不為盜，不見可欲，則民心不亂。常使民心無欲無惑，則無棄人矣。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 5,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 26
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "舉善以師不善，故謂之師矣。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 6,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "資，取也。善人以善齊不善，以善棄不善也。故不善人，善人之所取也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 7,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 15
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "雖有其智，自任其智，不因物，於其道必失。故曰，雖智大迷。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
